Early on Sunday morning, police gave chase after being alerted to a hijacking in Mfuleni in which a motorist was shot and wounded. CAPE TOWN - Three hijackers have been arrested in separate incidents in Cape Town. Early on Sunday morning, police gave chase after being alerted to a hijacking in Mfuleni in which a motorist was shot and wounded. During the pursuit, a pedestrian was knocked down and killed. One of the suspects was eventually arrested. Two accomplices were still at large. In a separate hijacking, a hijacker was shot and wounded in Khayelitsha. The man and another suspect were taken into custody.